by bicycle (in my next life I declare). I actually tried to hail a cab but getting a taxi is impossible in Budapest in the day time. It’s some kind of trend- to walk or take the bus- and apparently I did not master this trend. Whilst the scooter rental dude used (at least) 4 international languages (hungarian, italian, french, english) to give me tutorial of how to ride around under the blistering heat, I offered that I was wanting to, even though I was sweating my bum off. I returned in 1 piece- happily.

In a week that has been really stressful and things that I was all work in progress have come to a solidity. In Australia, pressing the flesh (literally) with auto screw machine is really sucky. As it is, the part that I hold is a bit thin and therefore I have suffered a few small cuts on my finger ’cause 7’12 fleck on my hand was touching the raw edges. Definitely unsure how to deal with this and wirelessly give the instructions to auto screw machine by having a second wire in my body? yeah I am on right track. Not.

On another note, meeting a friend from India was great and we had a great time together and I have found a great friend in him.
